00:10:32.780 --> 00:10:34.440
to hire slowly and quit quickly.

00:10:34.600 --> 00:10:35.560
Why are you hiring slowly?

00:10:36.120 --> 00:10:37.600
This is something that is sometimes

00:10:37.600 --> 00:10:39.720
very complicated in startups because

00:10:39.720 --> 00:10:41.180
you have to keep in mind that startups

00:10:41.180 --> 00:10:42.280
are companies that grow a lot

00:10:42.280 --> 00:10:43.680
in the first few years.

00:10:44.300 --> 00:10:46.860
That you move from founding partners

00:10:46.860 --> 00:10:49.500
to dozens of employees very quickly.

00:10:50.060 --> 00:10:51.800
Every day it seems like you need

00:10:51.800 --> 00:10:52.480
a new person.

00:10:52.540 --> 00:10:54.900
There is a tendency

00:10:54.900 --> 00:10:57.580
to hire too quickly.

00:10:58.600 --> 00:10:59.920
And really the recommendation

00:10:59.920 --> 00:11:00.920
is to be patient, to be patient

00:11:00.920 --> 00:11:03.800
because in addition the

00:11:03.800 --> 00:11:06.640
needs you have today of human

00:11:06.640 --> 00:11:09.160
capital may change tomorrow.

00:11:10.060 --> 00:11:11.440
Therefore, it is risky

00:11:11.440 --> 00:11:12.840
to hire every time a need

00:11:12.840 --> 00:11:13.480
arises.

