And I will explain why.

00:11:38.280 --> 00:11:39.480
I don't know if you know the world

00:11:39.480 --> 00:11:40.540
of startup, I don't know if you

00:11:40.540 --> 00:11:42.360
know the culture or some organization

00:11:42.600 --> 00:11:47.240
like that, but it's how the working

00:11:47.240 --> 00:11:48.480
environment and culture in

00:11:48.480 --> 00:11:49.800
a startup is very different from

00:11:49.800 --> 00:11:52.400
traditional companies for many reasons.

00:11:52.720 --> 00:11:54.340
It is a much more dynamic environment,

00:11:54.660 --> 00:11:55.720
opportunities are much greater,

00:11:55.720 --> 00:11:57.560
companies that grow are those that

00:11:57.560 --> 00:11:58.840
go well, they grow much more than

00:11:58.840 --> 00:12:00.420
traditional companies

00:12:00.420 --> 00:12:01.500
that are already in a mature

00:12:01.500 --> 00:12:03.380
market, in principle the

00:12:03.380 --> 00:12:04.100
growth is less.

00:12:05.500 --> 00:12:07.900
The challenge is bigger and the

00:12:07.900 --> 00:12:08.880
opportunities are bigger.

00:12:09.160 --> 00:12:11.180
It is also true that in some cases

00:12:11.180 --> 00:12:13.040
the companies when the working

00:12:13.040 --> 00:12:16.420
conditions are born are not

00:12:16.420 --> 00:12:17.020
so good.

00:12:17.200 --> 00:12:18.740
We look at it from an objective

00:12:18.740 --> 00:12:20.060
or traditional perspective.

00:12:20.640 --> 00:12:21.620
And the risk is even greater.

00:12:21.760 --> 00:12:22.560
So you have to look for people

00:12:22.560 --> 00:12:23.760
who are like the founders,

00:12:23.760 --> 00:12:25.700
who are microentrepreneurs.

00:12:26.500 --> 00:12:28.740
People who have a lot of

00:12:28.740 --> 00:12:29.520
